Class LuaRuntimeException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • net.sandius.rembulan.LuaRuntimeException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConversionException, IllegalCoroutineStateException, IllegalOperationAttemptException

    public class LuaRuntimeException
extends RuntimeException
    Base class for runtime exceptions that carry arbitrary error objects attached to them.

    To retrieve the error object, use getErrorObject().

    See Also:

      • LuaRuntimeException

        public LuaRuntimeException(Throwable cause)
        Constructs a new LuaRuntimeException with cause as its cause.

        When queried for the error object, invokes Conversions.toErrorObject(Throwable) on cause; when cause is null, then the error object is null.

        Parameters:
        cause - the cause of this error, may be null
